      • formatDistanceInMetricSystem

        public static java.lang.String formatDistanceInMetricSystem(android.content.Context context,
                                                            long distance)
        Converts a given distance in meters to a string representation rounded to meters or kilometers. Some examples:
        • If the given distance is greater than 10 km, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 1 km. For example, 10.37 km will be rounded to 10 km.
        • If the given distance is between 1 km and 10 km, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 100 m. For example, 9.37 km will be rounded to 9.30 km.
        • If the given distance is between 200 m and 1 km, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 50 m. For example, 340 m will be rounded to 300 m.
        • If the given distance is between 10 m and 200 m, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 10 m. For example, 165 m will be rounded to 170 m.
        • If the given distance is less than 10 m, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 1 m. For example, 1.3 m will be rounded to 1 m.
        Parameters:
        context - the required context.
        distance - the distance in meters.
        Returns:
        a string representation including unit.

      • formatDistanceInImperialUsSystem

        public static java.lang.String formatDistanceInImperialUsSystem(android.content.Context context,
                                                                long distance)
        Converts a given distance in meters to a string representation rounded to yards or miles. Some examples:
        • If the given distance is greater than 10 miles, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 1 mile. For example, 10.37 miles will be rounded to 10 miles.
        • If the given distance is between 1 mile and 10 miles, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 0.1 mile. For example, 9.37 miles will be rounded to 9.30 miles.
        • If the given distance is between 350 yd and 1 mile, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 50 yd. For example, 540 yd will be rounded to 500 yd.
        • If the given distance is between 10 yd and 350 yd, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 10 yd. For example, 132 yd will be rounded to 130 yd.
        • If the given distance is less than 10 yd, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 1 yd. For example, 1.3 yd will be rounded to 1 yd.
        Parameters:
        context - the required context.
        distance - the distance in meters.
        Returns:
        a string representation including unit.

        Converts a given distance in meters to a string representation rounded to feet or miles. Some examples:
        • If the given distance is greater than 10 miles, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 1 mile. For example, 10.37 miles will be rounded to 10 miles.
        • If the given distance is between 1 mile and 10 miles, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 0.1 mile. For example, 9.37 miles will be rounded to 9.30 miles.
        • If the given distance is between 1050 ft and 1 mile, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 50 ft. For example, 1240 ft will be rounded to 1200 ft.
        • If the given distance is between 10 ft and 1050 ft, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 10 ft. For example, 132 ft will be rounded to 130 ft.
        • If the given distance is less than 10 ft, then the returned value will be rounded to its nearest division of 1 ft. For example, 1.3 ft will be rounded to 1 ft.
